<table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0">
  <tr>
    <td class="tdheader">Critical Success Factors</td>
    <td class="tdheader">Critical Success Factor Assessment</td>
    <td class="tdheader">Get to Green Plan</td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Will the Client Buy?</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_0"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_0a">
                <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                <ul>
                    <li>What business issue(s) is the client trying to solve
                    and/or results trying to achieve?</li>
                    <li>What is the impact of these issues today, in terms of $$,
                    importance (1-10), or scale for the customer?</li>
                    <li>Does the client have a reasonable expectation of the time
                    required to complete the pursuit?</li>
                    <li>What happens if the client ignores this issue? What
                    alternatives do they have? (including do nothing)</li>
                </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_0b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Does the client have adequate funding and resources
                        available?</li>
                        <li>Who is the client sponsor? Do they have executive level
                        sponsorship?</li>
                        <li>Does the client have clarity on their decision making
                        process?</li>
                        <li>Is this initiative in the decision maker's performance
                        objectives and do they express an urgency to drive to completion?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                        <div id="csf_0c">
                            <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                            <ul>
                                <li>Has the client identified adequate funding/budget for the
                                solution?</li>
                                <li>Does the solution exactly meet the customer's
                                needs/business issues?</li>
                                <li>Are there any threats of the procurement being
                                challenged, and how do we mitigate?</li>
                            </ul>
                        </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_WTB__c}" style="height:100%;width:100%;" id="Comments_WTB" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Buyer Experience with HP</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_1"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_1a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What is the current book of business with HP and what is
                        the related client satisfaction rating? (Voice of the Client,
                        Relationship Assessment Process)</li>
                        <li>Who is in the decision process and have they bought from
                        HP prior to this opportunity?</li>
                        <li>What is the perception of HP? What has the customer
                        provided as feedback in surveys such as the Voice of the Client or
                        the RAP Scores.</li>
                        <li>If there is a sourcing advisor and/or consultant, what is
                        their experience with the client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_1b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>How does the client view HP across multiple levels?</li>
                        <li>How well developed is the account's ABP and customer
                        engagement? Have we demonstrated industry/business expertise?</li>
                        <li>If there is a sourcing advisor and/or consultant, how do
                        they view HP? How are they behaving toward HP? How is that
                        affecting the client’s view? What can we do to improve it?</li>
                        <li>Are alliance partners bringing value and any extra
                        advantage to the client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_1c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Is HP aligned to the client's strategic agenda? Does the
                        client view HP as reputable and capable?</li>
                        <li>If there is a sourcing advisor and/or consultant, how do
                        they view HP? How are they behaving toward HP? How is that
                        affecting the client’s view? What can we do to improve it?</li>
                        <li>How has the client’s view of HP shifted through the
                        pursuit process? What has caused that shift?</li>
                        <li>What should our proposal strategy be based on the
                        client's view of HP?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Buyer_Experience__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Client Relationship and Insight</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_2"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_2a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What does the initial Relationship Scorecard tell us
                        about HP's coverage with the key contacts on the opportunity? And
                        about their perception of HP?</li>
                        <li>Are there any political dynamics affecting the
                        scope/solution of this opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Has HP shared initial Value Proposition hypothesis with
                        key contacts and gained their agreement to next steps?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_2b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have we identified the power base and does the
                        relationship plan cover all of these contacts?</li>
                        <li>By what criteria are the key stakeholders making their
                        decisions?</li>
                        <li>What is the current delivery scenario (incumbent /
                        inhouse) and what are its challenges?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_2c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Does the Relationship Scorecard show strong positioning
                        of HP with the key contacts in the power base, and have we
                        identified all key roles for this opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Has the Value Proposition been discussed and agreed on by
                        key decision makers and influencers?</li>
                        <li>Does the proposal address the client's buying criteria
                        and is it satisfying key stakeholder's personal success criteria?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Client_Relationship__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Client Decision Process</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_3"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_3a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Who is driving the initiative within the client
                        organization?</li>
                        <li>Is the decision making centralized or de-centralized?</li>
                        <li>Has the client completed a transaction of this scope in
                        the past?</li>
                        <li>Is there a sourcing advisor and/or consultant involved,
                        if so, who? If not, are they needed?</li>
                        <li>What other items could have an impact on the decision
                        process? (I.e., regulatory authorities, works council, legal
                        advisors, etc.)</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_3b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Do we have a view into the customer's decision making
                        process (steps, decisions, when, who, criteria)?</li>
                        <li>What is the highest level of review and approval that
                        will be needed and do we have a relationship with them? (E.g.,
                        Board of Director, CEO, CFO, etc.)</li>
                        <li>Have we met and built a relationship with the person
                        signing the deal?</li>
                        <li>Who has empowered the decision maker to act on behalf of
                        the client organization?</li>
                        <li>If de-centralized, who are the major decision makers that
                        will need to support this solution? Have we identified them in the
                        relationship plan?</li>
                        <li>If the client has not done a deal of this size/scope, do
                        they understand what it will take to make it happen? Are we
                        working with the client to establish this process with/for them?</li>
                        <li>If there is a sourcing advisor and/or consultant, have we
                        met with them to understand the decision process and timeline?</li>
                        <li>Do we understand the decision criteria for each decision
                        maker and their weighting/importance?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_3c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Do we have the complete scope of the decision process
                        (steps, decisions, when, who, criteria)?</li>
                        <li>Have we established a relationship with the ultimate
                        decision maker, understand their criteria, and aligned the value
                        proposition?</li>
                        <li>Do we understand how a transaction of this size gets
                        decided on in this client organization?</li>
                        <li>Have we met with and have insights into all decision
                        makers business and personal agendas?</li>
                        <li>Do HP and the key decision makers have an agreed process
                        and are they actively working a process for the deal (large size
                        transaction)?</li>
                        <li>Does a close plan exist and has the client signed off on
                        it?</li>
                        <li>Has the team aligned the HP internal process to the
                        customer decision process? Are there any anticipated internal
                        approval challenges?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Client_Decision_Process__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Competitive Position</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_4"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_4a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Who are the competitors? Are any of these incumbent?</li>
                        <li>What is the status of the relationships with these
                        competitors in the account?</li>
                        <li>How well do HP strengths/capabilities align with the
                        client's business issue?</li>
                        <li>Does significant other business exist with HP and the
                        client?</li>
                        <li>Have we thought through creating significant barriers to
                        entry for the competition?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_4b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Is the client accepting the meetings from HP and engaging
                        with HP experts and executives openly, actively?</li>
                        <li>Can the client articulate the HP value proposition?</li>
                        <li>Do we have the price to win defined as part of a
                        competitive pricing strategy?</li>
                        <li>Has the HP team decided on the appropriate competitive
                        strategy and do we have plans in place to deploy?</li>
                        <li>Is the client using terminology or marketing words from a
                        competitor to describe the scope of services they want to buy?</li>
                        <li>Do we understand the sales strategy of our competitor and
                        plan to defeat?</li>
                        <li>Is the client using terminology or marketing words from a
                        competitor to describe the scope of services they want to buy?</li>
                        <li>Do we understand the sales strategy of our competitor and
                        plan to defeat?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_4c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Has the client confirmed the HP/client value proposition
                        and are they using it in their language internally?</li>
                        <li>How well is HP defending against the competitors' sales
                        strategies?</li>
                        <li>Have we validated the price to win/position to base case?
                        </li>
                        <li>Have we had the senior executive meetings with the
                        decision makers and key process owners to confirm position?</li>
                        <li>Have we confirmed we have the right team for the account?
                        </li>
                        <li>How is the Competitive Sales Plan, agreed previously,
                        going? What changes have occurred as a result of competitive
                        tactics and countertactics?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Competitive_Position__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Solution Scope</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_5"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_5a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have we gotten feedback from the client that the
                        potential solution could address their priority business issues?</li>
                        <li>Is the client strongly convinced this is the right
                        solution scope or approach and have we begun to educate them on
                        the HP Portfolio with references?</li>
                        <li>Have we identified the full context of who in the client
                        org could be affected by the solution?</li>
                        <li>Does HP believe there are more cost effective approaches
                        for the customer to achieve success, and have we shared the
                        alternatives?</li>
                        <li>Is the risk of delivering what they envision risky for HP
                        and its reputation or the client's business?</li>
                        <li>How will our competition respond and are they better
                        positioned?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_5b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have all key contacts in the decision making process
                        agreed to the solution scope and alignment to addressing business
                        issue(s)?</li>
                        <li>Have we delivered a solution like this before and do we
                        have solid references?</li>
                        <li>What are the alternatives the customer could consider?</li>
                        <li>What are the reasons that adopting the HP solution makes
                        sense for the client?</li>
                        <li>Have all the considerations of implementation and
                        transition been factored into the solution? (Who will be affected
                        across the client organization?)</li>
                        <li>Does our solution address the client's risks and/or
                        concerns?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_5c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Is the HP solution being viewed as a mutually developed
                        value proposition and will it address the customer's business
                        issues as they defined them?</li>
                        <li>How are solution, price to win, and proposed terms
                        validated against the client’s expectations / requirements?</li>
                        <li>Are there elements of the solution that can be
                        implemented in the current state (assuming current client)?</li>
                        <li>Can our solution be differentiated using HP Labs, key
                        strategic partners, or existing clients?</li>
                        <li>What is most important benefit to the client's success
                        that our solution highlights?</li>
                        <li>Is our solution scope less risky for the client, with a
                        simpler execution? Does our solution have less risk than the
                        competition's approach?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Solution_Scope__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Differentiation</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_6"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_6a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What are the potential unique competitive advantages HP
                        can employ to interest the client for this scope?</li>
                        <li>What short-term investments could be made to
                        differentiate the offering?</li>
                        <li>How can we differentiate the relationship to distinguish
                        our people in the minds of the client assessment and leadership
                        team?</li>
                        <li>What would we like to change about the opportunity to
                        allow HP to be able to provide a unique competitive advantage to
                        the client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_6b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What portfolio offerings, product design, industry
                        specific offerings, products and services when uniquely linked
                        together, or cost advantages can HP use to differentiate itself?</li>
                        <li>What are the differentiating strengths and weaknesses of
                        each known competitor that are unique to this client situation?</li>
                        <li>What is our specific plan for executive interaction to
                        build advantage into the relationship?</li>
                        <li>What executive options beyond the client request could
                        strengthen our proposal in the client’s mind? Are there latent
                        (unarticulated) needs that were discovered that allow HP to shift
                        the proposal toward HP competitive advantages?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_6c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Which offerings will be highlighted in the proposal that
                        clearly differentiate HP from competitors?</li>
                        <li>How will we, in the HP proposal and via our sales effort,
                        defend against competitive differentiation (tactics and
                        countertactics)?</li>
                        <li>What additional support is required from HP
                        leadership/executive sponsor to more deeply distinguish HP people
                        in the perspective of the client?</li>
                        <li>Would HP be able to command a proposal price premium,
                        need to provide pricing at parity, or need to be lower priced than
                        each competitor to win at this stage? Please provide evidence
                        about the degree of or lack of differentiation driving your
                        perspective.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Differentiation__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Teaming</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_7"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_7a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What are the client’s requirements around teaming?</li>
                        <li>Are there any incumbent service providers? How are they
                        liked by the client/performance? Would we consider them a
                        competitor or partner?</li>
                        <li>Are there any unique client requirements that require
                        specific domain expertise that HP does not hold?</li>
                        <li>Which companies have key relationships with the client?
                        (I.e., audit or other supplier or business partner relationship)</li>
                        <li>What does an HP “Dream Team” look like from the client’s
                        perspective?</li>
                        <li>Is our teaming approach focused on low cost or best value
                        and innovation?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_7b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What is the current make-up of the HP team and status of
                        Teaming Agreements? What is the level of commitment from our
                        partners? (I.e., senior level relationships with partner)
                        Exclusivity on any Teaming Agreements?</li>
                        <li>Have we been able to confirm the client’s preferences on
                        teaming? Does our team make-up address the client’s business
                        drivers?</li>
                        <li>What are the gaps in our capability to deliver these
                        services, and what partners (incumbent or otherwise) do we still
                        need to fill gaps?</li>
                        <li>Are we engaged in joint sales/solution activities with
                        key partners?</li>
                        <li>Are necessary fire-wall protections in place with HP
                        segments?</li>
                        <!-- Commented By Vinay S for ALM #:3464                    
                        <li>Can the teaming partners help us perform a black hat
                        and/or participate in our win strategy lab?</li>
                             --> 
                      <li>Can the teaming partners help us perform a black hat 
                      and/or engage in workshop?</li>
                      <li>Is the client open to innovation? If so, what partners do
                        they perceive as bringing them innovation or fresh ideas?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_7c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have our partners committed dedicated resources to the
                        bid?</li>
                        <li>Are teammate performance commitments on track?</li>
                        <li>Are there any solutioning challenges with our partners?</li>
                        <li>Are there any pricing challenges from our partners
                        relative to Price to Win?</li>
                        <li>What role will the partners have in our solutioning,
                        writing, references, and red team?</li>
                        <li>How do we elicit the proposal support we need and
                        discriminators that teaming partners bring and get that content
                        into the proposal?</li>
                        <li>Do we still believe we have addressed the client’s
                        preferences on teaming and validated that needs remain the same as
                        compared to the start of the pursuit?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Teaming__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Sales Team Staffing</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_8"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_8a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Do we have the right industry representation on the team
                        to properly validate the opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Do we have the right technical representation on the
                        team?</li>
                        <li>How would the client view our capabilities in this
                        industry?</li>
                        <li>Do we have any executive relationships that can help
                        validate this opportunity with the client?</li>
                        <li>Who is leading it from a sales perspective (account,
                        sales, sales leadership)?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_8b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Has the right industry team fully qualified the
                        opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Has the right technical team assessed the opportunity and
                        can we meet the client's expectation?</li>
                        <li>Do we have the team it would take to win this
                        opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Are they available to pursue the opportunity?</li>
                        <li>Who is leading the sales effort (sales exec, strategic
                        sales exec)?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_8c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have we filled all of the pursuit team positions?</li>
                        <li>Do we have the A team on the opportunity? What is the
                        quality of each relationship?</li>
                        <li>Do we have the executive support from a relationship
                        perspective?</li>
                        <li>How is the team perceived by the client?</li>
                        <li>Is HP competitively positioned to win, and do we have
                        differentiation with our sales/industry/delivery team?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Sales_Team_Staffing__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Deal Shape and Pricing</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_9"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_9a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Does the client have an idea of what price range they
                        expect to see from HP/our competitors based on the scope of the
                        deal at this stage? Have we asked the client for this information?</li>
                        <li>Do we have an initial view on our ability to achieve the
                        client’s expected price range based on our initial assessment of
                        what our proposed solution scope would look like?</li>
                        <li>Has the client purchased these services before, e.g.
                        subsidiary, other geography? Do they already have an internal
                        benchmark for the services that they wish to purchase?</li>
                        <li>Do we have an view, based on an initial understanding of
                        a deal structure, of how our pricing will compare to our
                        competitors’ prices? What is the basis for this view?</li>
                        <li>Is the client looking at price from a Total Cost of
                        Ownership (TCO) perspective? If not, how can they be steered in
                        this direction? I.e., do we/client have a view of current assets,
                        premises costs, depreciation policies, and likely cost/structure
                        of retained organization?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_9b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What is our level of confidence that we have the
                        Competitive Price Range correct? Why do we believe that we are
                        tracking accurately to a Competitive Price Range?</li>
                        <li>Other than client guidance what reference data inputs are
                        we using to determine that our Competitive Price Range is correct?</li>
                        <li>Please demonstrate how we are managing our “glide path”
                        from initial pricing submission to land at Competitive Price Range
                        at Best and Final Offer (BAFO) through RFI/RFP phases i.e.
                        credibility factor with client team?</li>
                        <li>Based on our proposed solution, can the services the
                        client is requesting be benchmarked easily, will it be possible to
                        obtain market pricing to support future price discussions?</li>
                        <li>Have we identified any specific structural
                        advantage/disadvantage against competitors, e.g. competitor’s need
                        to use 3rd parties for services such as “break-fix” driving margin
                        on margin issues, ability to include other HP Services that can be
                        exploited – HP Finance, etc in our price?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_9c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>When did we last discuss Competitive Price Range range
                        with client and at what level in client organization?</li>
                        <li>What is our level confidence that we now have the
                        Competitive Price Range correct prior to BAFO submission?</li>
                        <li>What price do we expect our primary competitor bid at?
                        What is the basis of our understanding?</li>
                        <li>Have we been able to establish Total Cost of Ownership
                        (TCO) position with client to ensure a like for like comparison
                        with our primary competitor? Can we articulate clear value based
                        differentials for HP?</li>
                        <li>Does our Competitive Price Range meet corporate
                        margins/metrics for associated risk? If not on what basis are we
                        requesting support from senior management to approve submission at
                        Competitive Price Range i.e. what is our recovery plan/risk
                        mitigation plan post contract signature?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Deal_Shape_and_Pricing__c}"
                            style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Delivery Leadership Team</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_10"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_10a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Have we given thought to identifying a delivery leader
                        and team?</li>
                        <li>How rapidly will the pursuit progress? When do we need to
                        begin preparation for transition and delivery?</li>
                        <li>When will we need to put our delivery people in front of
                        the customer to describe our solution approach?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_10b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Do we have candidates identified that are knowledgeable
                        and credible?</li>
                        <li>Do we understand their availability issues?</li>
                        <li>Have we ensured the delivery candidates have a full
                        understanding of the value proposition with the client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_10c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Are delivery team candidates identified and available to
                        work with the pursuit team in presenting a solution to the
                        customer?</li>
                        <li>Is the defined delivery leader on board, been thoroughly
                        briefed on the solution, and met with the client to begin
                        establishing relationships?</li>
                        <li>Are the candidates polished and effective in front of the
                        customer?</li>
                        <li>Are the candidates available if a positive decision is
                        made by the customer to proceed to down-select?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Delivery_Leadership_Team__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
  <tr>
    <td class="tdcsf">Terms and Conditions</td>
    <td style="padding: 10px;"><select id="ass_11"></select>
        <br />
        <div id="csf_11a">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>What do the client requirements (RFI, RFP, scope
                        document, etc.) tell us about the client's approach to terms and
                        conditions? If nonstandard, have you researched acceptable
                        alternatives?</li>
                        <li>What challenges/issues have arisen in discussions to
                        date? What mitigation strategies have you identified to address
                        potential future conflicts early in order to prevent last moment
                        concessions? How will these strategies affect the deal's risk
                        profile?</li>
                       <!-- Commented By Vinay S for ALM #:3464                    
                        <li>Does HP have an existing relationship with this client in ES or other HP Business Units? &#91;NOTE: Product T&#38;C's are
                        likely not going to be relevant to ES, but client posture and
                        level of difficulty in negotiation would be an indicator.&#93;
                        Does the applicable contract and/or the client relationship
                        history provide insight into the client's attitudes and expectations?</li>
                             -->  
                     <li>Does HP have an existing relationship with any HP Business Units?
                         &#91;NOTE: Product T&#38;C's are likely not going to be relevant to ES, but client 
                         posture and level of difficulty in negotiation would be an indicator.] Does the 
                         applicable contract and/or the client relationship history provide insight into the 
                         client's attitudes and expectations? </li>

                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_11b">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Are we talking to budget owners vs. centralized IT (who
                        often is a reseller of our services). If decentralized, will you
                        proposed a sufficiently robust governance structure that includes
                        client internal complementary obligations/responsibilities?</li>
                        <li>Are client demands in line with revenue/profit
                        opportunity? How confident are you that HP can overcome the
                        T&#38;C challenges without eroding deal value?</li>
                        <li>Are all terms that have an impact on the deal risk rating
                        identified and proposed mitigations documented? Based on your
                        assessment of the T&#38;C risks/issues identified to date, should
                        HP make further investments in this pursuit to reach a compromise
                        agreement with client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
                <div id="csf_11c">
                    <p><b>Criteria:</b></p>
                    <ul>
                        <li>Are all terms that have an impact on the deal risk rating
                        documented and resolved? If not, how many major issues remain, and
                        what are they?</li>
                        <li>What is the estimated impact of the open major issues? Is
                        the pricing strategy appropriate to the risk level? [Note: If we
                        are selling on price, keep things generic with add-on service
                        menu.]</li>
                        <li>What is your strategy to negotiate existing challenges?
                        What is the estimated impact of this strategy on deal
                        value/performance? Is the entire HP Executive Sponsor chain on
                        board with the proposed mitigation strategy?</li>
                        <li>If there are approved variances from HP standards, how
                        are the appropriate mitigation and execution approaches
                        incorporated into the proposal?</li>
                        <li>Is the entire HP Executive Sponsor chain aligned with the
                        T&#38;C's negotiation strategy to ensure one face to the client?</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
    </td>
    <td class="tdgtgp"><apex:inputfield value="{!Opportunity_Plan__c.DHC_Comments_Terms_and_Conditions__c}"
                        style="height:100%;width:100%;" /></td>
  </tr>
